---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import { CHANNEL_URL, CHANNEL_HANDLE } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
	title="About Shed Flips"
	description="Lonnie and Candice flip garage-sale and estate-sale finds online — eBay, Mercari, Etsy, Poshmark, wherever they land best."
	pubDate={new Date('April 29 2026')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>Shed Flips</strong> is Lonnie and Candice — a husband-and-wife team who source items at
		garage sales, estate sales, auctions, and thrift stores, then flip them online (eBay, Mercari,
		Etsy, Poshmark, wherever the item lands best). The shed is where it all happens: the staging,
		the photography, the listing, the packing.
	</p>

	<p>
		Each post here is a written companion to a video on the channel — for people who'd rather
		skim a haul list, look up a sold price, or revisit a strategy talk than rewind through a
		20-minute video. The video is always embedded at the top of every post, so you can watch,
		read, or both.
	</p>

	<h2>What you'll find here</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>Hauls from real days at real sales — what we paid, what we picked, what we passed on</li>
		<li>Sold-stats wrap-ups: what moved on which platform and for how much</li>
		<li>Strategy notes from years of doing this — pricing, photos, listing copy, fees</li>
		<li>Lessons learned the hard way — shipping cost surprises, condition mistakes, all of it</li>
		<li>Links back to the source video on YouTube</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Subscribe</h2>

	<p>
		New videos drop on the YouTube channel at <a href={CHANNEL_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener"
			>{CHANNEL_HANDLE}</a
		>. If you prefer to read, follow along here — every post links back to the video, and there's
		an <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> if that's your thing.
	</p>
</Layout>
